values:
Modern, Cool Nerd
73 % Nerd, 52% Geek, 34% Dork
For The Record:

A Nerd is someone who is passionate about learning/being smart/academia.
A Geek is someone who is passionate about some particular area or subject, often an obscure or difficult one.
A Dork is someone who has difficulty with common social expectations/interactions.
You scored better than half in Nerd and Geek, earning you the title of: Modern, Cool Nerd.

Nerds didn't use to be cool, but in the 90's that all changed. It used to be that, if you were a computer expert, you had to wear plaid or a pocket protector or suspenders or something that announced to the world that you couldn't quite fit in. Not anymore. Now, the intelligent and geeky have eked out for themselves a modicum of respect at the very least, and "geek is chic." The Modern, Cool Nerd is intelligent, knowledgable and always the person to call in a crisis (needing computer advice/an arcane bit of trivia knowledge). They are the one you want as your lifeline in Who Wants to Be a Millionaire (or the one up there, winning the million bucks)!

Congratulations!


Also, you might want to check out some of my other tests if you're interested in any of the following:

Buffy the Vampire Slayer

Well, my new years was fantastic!  Jennifer and I went to see King Kong together, I don't know which was better: The movie or the 3 hours of cuddling... I suppose if I'm a real man the answer to that question should be obvious, but I'll leave it open :)

Now I'm back into the grind of classes and thesis writing, fuck me sideways!  My social life is about as shot as well, somebody who just got executed firing squad style.  I think the only human contact I'll be getting is picking Jennifer up for class on the Tuesdays I have a car.  Other than that I'm a social outcast until April 5th at Noon...

Dear God am I looking forward to the trip Jennifer and I are planning...  I don't care where we go, I just want to get away from EVERYTHING!!!  Not necessarily my friends of course, but I just want to leave work, and normalcy behind.  I suppose I should start shedding off about 50 more lbs so I can look beach worthy, lol.

Well, that's enough of a rant from yours truly :)  My mind is full of all kinds of things, one thing in particular that will happen in August, oh and of course my Medschool interview on February 3rd, but mostly August...

Cheers

I had an amazing day with Jennifer on Friday.  It started with her calling to make sure I was doing ok because we had to put our doggy down the night before, I really appreciated that call.

Then I picked her up from class at 12:30 (like the good chauffeur I am) and we headed to her place.  It took us awhile to get there because of an accident on the 102, but after listening to a few songs from my MP3 player that Jennifer picked we finally made it to her place.

Once there I gave Jennifer's mom a huge bouquet of flowers for her Birthday, I put her name on the card but Jennifer informed me that I should've put "Mom" on the card, so apparently Jennifer's cool with me calling her mom "Mom" though she explicitly stated to never call her Dad "Dad" lol, which is understandable, I wouldn't want some guy calling me Dad if he was dating my daughter.

So that evening I cooked supper for their family, I made my patented Lasagna which everybody seemed to really enjoy, even her dad, who doesn't like pasta.

On another note her Dad also said that I'm no longer company, so that's pretty cool.

Jennifer and I also decided (well, she suggested and I agreed) that we should not buy movies that the other person has bought or will buy, she said it only makes sense, which is true.  I thought that was a pretty big step in our relationship because both of us are movieholics and we love our movie collections so to be ready to combine our collections is a pretty big thing and it gives me great hope for the future.

After supper we watched Donny Darko, that was a pretty fucked up movie but I enjoyed it because you never quite knew what was going on.

I think that's about it aside from the fact that she looked amazing in her new jeans, they definitely get a "shaaaaawing" on the Wayne's world scale of hotness.

This is probably the longest update I've ever made, lol...

Cheers,
Jonathan

Hey Jenn,in response to your live journal posting.  How about when you have a problem with how I do something you talk to me about it instead of ranting to the entire world first?  I may have lacked a little finesse in my interpersonal skills that day, but as someone who also works in the customer service industry I say this to you "Get over yourself".  At the age of 21 if you can't introduce yourself to somebody then I'm afraid, my friend, that there is not much hope for you at all.  I can't be held responsible for a mistake, you know I rarely introduce people, and for fuck sakes, she always sits next to me, get a grip on reality woman...  And as for Jennifer, don't get mad at me because I haven't brought her to the SUB yet, she has a life to you know.  Just because I'm her boyfriend doesn't change how much schoolwork she has or the way she deals with how much schoolwork she has.  School comes before a relationship, or at least it should, because without a future there can be no future between couples.  So for the last time, and I'm not sure I want her to be subjected to you anymore, I will get her to the SUB when/if I can.  But if you're going to be all high and mighty, I don't know if I want her to meet you.  Don't think of this as me being mean to you, think of it as somebody being rude to me behind my back, and guess what I don't tolerate?  That's right, 2 things in this world, somebody being rude behind my back and stupidity, guess which two of the above two you have portrayed?  I'm only posting this on LJ because I know you read it on a daily basis whereas I never read mine which is why you should've told me to my face.  I don't expect an apology, I expect understanding that I'm not a perfect human being and that mistakes are made and if you notice these mistakes than I oblige you to inform me of them.

Cheers, and good luck with your degree,
Jonathan
